<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05079f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05079f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05079f"> 79(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Kevin sleeps on sowskin </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: The life of the monks was one of great austerity and activity, and it was provided that at all times during the day when they were not occupied at prayer they should be engaged on some work for the community or for the people whom they served. <mark>They slept on the bare ground or on a skin laid on a little straw or rushes</mark>. St. Columcille and St. Ciaran of Clonmacnoise had stones for their pillows. </mm> </dd></dl>
